<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-01-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="450" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d450">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Hale</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 55.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-01-28"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 28, 1867.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 7th instant, No. 74,
                            has been received. Your execution of my instruction No. 52, proposing
                            mediation on the part of the United States for the arrangement of the
                            pending difficulties between Spain and the allied South American States,
                            is entirely satisfactory. We have as yet heard nothing from the other
                            belligerents, but their reply when received will be promptly
                            communicated to you.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">John P. Hale</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>